1
00:00:00,667 --> 00:00:02,377
Previously Riverdale...

2
00:00:02,419 --> 00:00:04,004
Do you see those people
over there?

3
00:00:04,045 --> 00:00:05,422
They're Dodger's family.

4
00:00:05,463 --> 00:00:07,590
I'm not sure
what you're here for,

5
00:00:07,632 --> 00:00:09,175
but you and your boys
need to leave.

6
00:00:09,217 --> 00:00:11,177
We've got kids here,
we don't want any trouble.

7
00:00:11,219 --> 00:00:13,680
Mr. DuPont, the first book
in the Baxter Brothers series,

8
00:00:13,722 --> 00:00:15,515
was written by my grandfather.

9
00:00:15,557 --> 00:00:16,891
I killed Caramel.

10
00:00:16,933 --> 00:00:20,228
No, Betty, that wasn't you,

11
00:00:20,270 --> 00:00:22,605
that was your deeply
screwed-up dad.

12
00:00:22,647 --> 00:00:24,357
Someone is trying
to drive me mad.

13
00:00:24,399 --> 00:00:27,444
But, once I find out
who this depraved monster is,

14
00:00:27,485 --> 00:00:29,654
I will unleash a wrath
upon them so wicked,

15
00:00:29,696 --> 00:00:32,282
they will wish they had been
consumed in their mother's womb.

16
00:00:32,323 --> 00:00:34,200
You've reached
the Riverdale hotline.

17
00:00:34,242 --> 00:00:37,537
If you wish to report a problem in
your neighborhood, leave a message.

18
00:00:37,579 --> 00:00:40,206
Anonymity is your choice.
We're here to help.

19
00:00:41,875 --> 00:00:45,378
"And as Buddy and Bobby Baxter sat
down at the dining room table,"

20
00:00:45,420 --> 00:00:47,255
exhausted and bruised,

21
00:00:47,297 --> 00:00:49,591
they felt satisfaction.

22
00:00:49,632 --> 00:00:52,218
The Case of the Boy
in the River had been solved.

23
00:00:52,260 --> 00:00:54,804
Tomorrow, there would be
another mystery.

24
00:00:54,846 --> 00:00:58,141
But tonight, their only concern

25
00:00:58,183 --> 00:00:59,309
"was dinner."

26
00:01:02,771 --> 00:01:04,981
Outstanding, Mr. Jones.

27
00:01:05,023 --> 00:01:08,318
I believe the Baxter Brothers has
found their newest ghostwriter.

28
00:01:09,319 --> 00:01:10,904
Wait, I won the contract?

29
00:01:10,945 --> 00:01:12,614
Like, right this second?

30
00:01:12,655 --> 00:01:13,239
That is correct.

31
00:01:13,240 --> 00:01:16,493
Professor DuPont,
you can't actually believe

32
00:01:16,534 --> 00:01:18,411
that garbage was better
than my submission.

33
00:01:18,453 --> 00:01:20,497
Oh, I can and I do.

34
00:01:21,623 --> 00:01:23,958
Your contract, Mr. Jones.

35
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:27,003
Your first step into
a larger, better life.

36
00:01:27,045 --> 00:01:28,922
Provided you play by the rules.

37
00:01:36,262 --> 00:01:39,599
I don't understand.
Dartmouth was my safety school.

38
00:01:39,641 --> 00:01:42,602
I guess you should've
accepted Harvard's invitation.

39
00:01:43,812 --> 00:01:45,271
Nice try, Daddy,

40
00:01:45,313 --> 00:01:47,190
but I still have
my interview with Columbia.

41
00:01:48,066 --> 00:01:49,359
Interview, huh?

42
00:01:50,151 --> 00:01:51,736
Good luck with that.

43
00:01:51,778 --> 00:01:54,656
Columbia's
extremely competitive.

44
00:01:54,697 --> 00:01:58,535
But, I believe
Riverdale Community College

45
00:01:58,576 --> 00:02:01,121
has a rolling admission policy.

46
00:02:01,162 --> 00:02:04,290
So if you study there,
you could launch your rum empire.

47
00:02:05,166 --> 00:02:06,459
If that's still happening.

48
00:02:06,501 --> 00:02:08,211
Oh, it's happening, Daddy.

49
00:02:11,965 --> 00:02:13,716
Hey, wake up, Red.

50
00:02:14,717 --> 00:02:18,054
Mr. Jones? Ah!
What are you doing here?

51
00:02:18,096 --> 00:02:20,640
Investigating a vigilante.

52
00:02:20,682 --> 00:02:23,226
Now be honest with me.
Is that you?

53
00:02:24,269 --> 00:02:25,812
Yeah, it is.

54
00:02:25,854 --> 00:02:27,123
You're not gonna
arrest me, are you?

55
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:28,231
I should.

56
00:02:30,859 --> 00:02:32,503
What the hell do you think
you're doing, huh?

57
00:02:32,527 --> 00:02:33,403
Helping.

58
00:02:33,404 --> 00:02:36,823
People are too scared to call you
or the cops, so I set up a hotline.

59
00:02:37,991 --> 00:02:40,326
What happens if you get hurt?
Or worse?

60
00:02:40,368 --> 00:02:43,329
People die changing tires on
the side of the road, Mr. Jones.

61
00:02:43,371 --> 00:02:44,849
At least I'd die with
a shred of honor.

62
00:02:44,873 --> 00:02:47,000
[SCOFFS] What a load of smug BS.

63
00:02:47,041 --> 00:02:49,544
You think that's gonna
comfort your mom?

64
00:02:49,586 --> 00:02:51,337
Why aren't you focused
on the center,

65
00:02:51,379 --> 00:02:53,381
- protecting these kids?
- I am.

66
00:02:53,423 --> 00:02:55,842
But trouble shows up here
about every other day,

67
00:02:55,884 --> 00:02:58,720
starting with the Dickensons who
are still out there, by the way.

68
00:02:58,761 --> 00:03:00,722
You're doing
good work here, Red.

69
00:03:00,763 --> 00:03:03,057
Here. Honorable work.

70
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:06,519
Maybe I can help you.

71
00:03:06,561 --> 00:03:08,372
[JUGHEAD] What do you say, Chuck.
Can you help me?

72
00:03:08,396 --> 00:03:10,481
So you want me
to use FBI resources

73
00:03:10,523 --> 00:03:12,275
to track down your...

74
00:03:12,317 --> 00:03:14,402
Sorry, our grandfather.

75
00:03:15,236 --> 00:03:16,154
Why the sudden urgency?

76
00:03:16,155 --> 00:03:19,449
Well, look, it's probably something
I should have done months ago, but...

77
00:03:20,491 --> 00:03:22,118
I have an important
decision to make.

78
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:24,287
And I can't until I know the truth.
His truth.

79
00:03:25,455 --> 00:03:26,455
Can you help me?

80
00:03:27,290 --> 00:03:27,790
What's wrong, Pop?

81
00:03:27,791 --> 00:03:30,293
Our liquor license
has been revoked.

82
00:03:30,335 --> 00:03:33,713
As of Sunday, the speakeasy won't
be allowed to serve alcohol.

83
00:03:33,755 --> 00:03:35,256
What? According to whom?

84
00:03:35,298 --> 00:03:36,716
The mayor's office.

85
00:03:36,758 --> 00:03:38,718
Figures.

86
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:41,054
This is payback
for me vowing to challenge.

87
00:03:41,095 --> 00:03:42,931
Daddy's precious rum empire.

88
00:03:42,972 --> 00:03:45,808
Long-term,
we're fighting this injunction.

89
00:03:46,726 --> 00:03:48,311
Short-term,

90
00:03:50,063 --> 00:03:52,106
we're hosting
a no-holds barred blow-out

91
00:03:52,148 --> 00:03:54,317
at La Bonne Nuit
before the boom falls.

92
00:03:55,902 --> 00:03:57,612
No offense, Veronica,

93
00:03:57,654 --> 00:04:00,657
but your father,
he wasn't raised right.

94
00:04:02,784 --> 00:04:04,160
Actually,

95
00:04:04,619 --> 00:04:06,788
he was.

96
00:04:06,829 --> 00:04:09,791
And you've just given me
a great idea.

97
00:04:12,502 --> 00:04:14,003
[CREAKING]

98
00:04:14,045 --> 00:04:16,089
Betty. Betty, wake up.

99
00:04:16,130 --> 00:04:17,632
What? What's happening?

100
00:04:17,674 --> 00:04:19,259
Honey, it's your sister.

101
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:21,010
She mutilated a nurse
at Shady Grove.

102
00:04:21,052 --> 00:04:22,637
She almost clawed her face off.

103
00:04:25,139 --> 00:04:26,641
[BETTY] Maybe this is a mistake.

104
00:04:26,683 --> 00:04:29,852
Polly's messed up,
but she's not a literal monster.

105
00:04:29,894 --> 00:04:32,105
This is security footage

106
00:04:32,146 --> 00:04:33,189
from Shady Grove.

107
00:04:34,107 --> 00:04:35,400
[BETTY SIGHS]

108
00:04:38,820 --> 00:04:42,532
Okay, Polly is sitting there, looking
like a zombie, but she's not hurt...

109
00:04:49,497 --> 00:04:51,958
Oh, my God. Oh, my God!

110
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:55,461
What the hell happened?
She attacked that nurse for no reason.

111
00:04:55,503 --> 00:04:57,255
She'll only talk to you,
she says.

112
00:04:58,006 --> 00:04:58,506
And alone.

113
00:04:58,548 --> 00:04:59,999
Okay. Well then
I'll go talk to her.

114
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,026
Okay. Well then
I'll go talk to her.

115
00:05:01,050 --> 00:05:03,344
First, there's one more thing
you should know.

116
00:05:03,386 --> 00:05:05,179
The nurse that Polly disfigured,

117
00:05:06,306 --> 00:05:07,348
her name is Betty.

118
00:05:09,517 --> 00:05:11,978
Heard you wanted to speak to me.

119
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:15,815
Betty. Oh, thank God.

120
00:05:15,857 --> 00:05:19,110
You're the one I can trust.
Can you tell me what's going on?

121
00:05:19,152 --> 00:05:20,987
Polly, can you tell me
what's going on?

122
00:05:21,029 --> 00:05:23,656
You attacked
a nurse named Betty.

123
00:05:23,698 --> 00:05:24,991
That's impossible.

124
00:05:25,033 --> 00:05:28,328
I can't remember
any of what they're saying.

125
00:05:28,369 --> 00:05:30,830
I was in the rec room,
and the next thing I remember,

126
00:05:30,872 --> 00:05:32,999
I'm in here
and I'm chained to this bed.

127
00:05:33,041 --> 00:05:35,084
Please, Betty.

128
00:05:35,126 --> 00:05:36,961
You have to believe me,
Betty, please.

129
00:05:37,503 --> 00:05:38,713
I didn't do this.

130
00:05:38,755 --> 00:05:39,547
Please believe me.

131
00:05:39,589 --> 00:05:43,634
I didn't do it, Betty.
I didn't do it, it wasn't me. [CRYING]

132
00:05:43,676 --> 00:05:45,636
Please, I didn't do it.
I didn't do this, Betty.

133
00:05:45,678 --> 00:05:46,678
I didn't do it.

134
00:05:53,978 --> 00:05:56,439
Damn, Mr. Jones,
where did you get a metal detector?

135
00:05:56,481 --> 00:05:58,161
From Southside High
when they shut it down,

136
00:05:58,191 --> 00:06:00,461
but between that,
and the security cameras we're hooking up,

137
00:06:00,485 --> 00:06:02,028
think you're in
pretty good shape, Red.

138
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:03,946
Yeah, well, I'll be
in even better shape

139
00:06:03,988 --> 00:06:06,050
once Dodger and his family
are in jail or out of town.

140
00:06:06,074 --> 00:06:08,534
But all this is awesome.
Thank you, sir.

141
00:06:08,576 --> 00:06:10,870
Hey, uh, I can
help you find Dodger.

142
00:06:10,912 --> 00:06:13,247
I know the alleys,
and a bunch of us used to work for him.

143
00:06:13,289 --> 00:06:14,082
We're good, Eddie.

144
00:06:14,083 --> 00:06:18,419
The last thing I need is you
out there kicking up dust, okay?

145
00:06:18,461 --> 00:06:20,088
[VERONICA] Abuelita.

146
00:06:20,129 --> 00:06:23,299
[LORDES] You've been so busy
mi ahijada.

147
00:06:24,092 --> 00:06:25,885
- Godmother.
- Mm?

148
00:06:25,927 --> 00:06:29,430
I've been thinking about
expanding my business,

149
00:06:29,472 --> 00:06:31,724
getting into rum production.

150
00:06:31,766 --> 00:06:33,226
But there's a real craft to it,

151
00:06:33,267 --> 00:06:36,187
and my father
refuses to teach me.

152
00:06:37,188 --> 00:06:39,399
- How did he learn?
- From me.

153
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:41,984
It is my recipe that he's using.

154
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:44,987
Could you tell me the recipe?

155
00:06:45,029 --> 00:06:46,989
[CHUCKLING] Of course!

156
00:06:48,825 --> 00:06:50,410
But what about college?

157
00:06:51,452 --> 00:06:53,204
Have you heard back
from Harvard?

158
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:55,289
Abuelita,

159
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,917
you won't even believe,

160
00:06:57,959 --> 00:07:00,628
the things that your son
has been doing.

161
00:07:01,295 --> 00:07:02,505
What kind of things?

162
00:07:05,675 --> 00:07:07,301
[PHONE VIBRATES]

163
00:07:07,343 --> 00:07:08,886
Hey, Charles, any luck?

164
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:09,679
Yeah. I found him.

165
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:11,973
More specifically,
the U.S. Postal Service did.

166
00:07:12,014 --> 00:07:13,850
Wait, seriously? How?

167
00:07:13,891 --> 00:07:17,019
Evidently, Forsythe has
a P.O. box in Seaside.

168
00:07:17,061 --> 00:07:19,206
He checks it once a month when
he comes in from the forest.

169
00:07:19,230 --> 00:07:21,107
Wait, did you say forest?

170
00:07:21,149 --> 00:07:23,609
The crazy thing is,
I actually believe her.

171
00:07:23,651 --> 00:07:25,361
Honey, we saw it
with our own eyes.

172
00:07:25,403 --> 00:07:27,780
Well, no, obviously,
she did it, but...

173
00:07:28,489 --> 00:07:29,198
not consciously.

174
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:33,536
It's like she was fuguing or something.
Wait a minute.

175
00:07:33,578 --> 00:07:36,789
The doctors at Shady Grove said
Polly received a phone call

176
00:07:36,831 --> 00:07:39,876
about an hour or so
before the incident.

177
00:07:40,418 --> 00:07:43,254
[PHONE RINGING]

178
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:45,882
Charles is trying to figure
out the caller's identity.

179
00:07:47,008 --> 00:07:49,969
[PHONE CONTINUES RINGING]

180
00:07:50,011 --> 00:07:51,596
Cooper-Jones residence.

181
00:07:59,854 --> 00:08:01,772
What? Was it about Polly?

182
00:08:13,159 --> 00:08:14,410
What are you doing?

183
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:17,747
What are you doing?

184
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:19,540
Mom.

185
00:08:19,582 --> 00:08:21,292
Listen to... Mom!

186
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:24,253
You're acting just like Polly.

187
00:08:24,295 --> 00:08:26,672
You're acting hypnotized.

188
00:08:27,381 --> 00:08:28,549
[CLAPS HANDS]

189
00:08:33,054 --> 00:08:34,972
What's going on?
Why am I holding a knife?

190
00:08:36,390 --> 00:08:38,017
You don't remember?

191
00:08:38,059 --> 00:08:39,477
Did somebody...

192
00:08:40,561 --> 00:08:42,230
Did the phone ring,
or did I imagine it?

193
00:08:42,271 --> 00:08:44,690
No, it rang, you answered...

194
00:08:44,732 --> 00:08:47,568
Whoever called must have
said something that...

195
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:50,655
I don't know, triggered you
into attacking me.

196
00:08:50,696 --> 00:08:51,864
Is that even possible?

197
00:08:53,574 --> 00:08:55,618
We need Charles
to trace that phone call.

198
00:09:01,082 --> 00:09:02,208
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]

199
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:03,793
Mami.

200
00:09:03,834 --> 00:09:05,962
What a surprise.
When did you get here?

201
00:09:06,796 --> 00:09:08,089
[SHOUTS IN SPANISH]

202
00:09:09,090 --> 00:09:10,841
You should be
ashamed of yourself.

203
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:13,970
Picking fights
with your daughter.

204
00:09:14,011 --> 00:09:16,472
Your father is turning over
in his grave.

205
00:09:19,225 --> 00:09:20,393
[FOOTSTEPS DEPART]

206
00:09:23,771 --> 00:09:25,064
Really?

207
00:09:25,106 --> 00:09:27,066
Turning my own mother
against me.

208
00:09:27,942 --> 00:09:29,277
Oh.

209
00:09:29,318 --> 00:09:31,904
And guess what
she shared with me.

210
00:09:31,946 --> 00:09:34,240
Our family's secret rum recipe.

211
00:09:36,075 --> 00:09:38,160
So brace yourself, Daddy.

212
00:09:38,202 --> 00:09:39,328
It's on.

213
00:09:42,290 --> 00:09:44,292
Archie, I need
for you to sit down for this.

214
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:48,337
Vic, your dad's foreman,

215
00:09:48,379 --> 00:09:49,922
came by earlier today

216
00:09:49,964 --> 00:09:54,093
and he wants to buy us
out of Andrews Construction.

217
00:09:54,135 --> 00:09:56,429
Well, tough, Mom,
'cause we're not selling.

218
00:09:56,470 --> 00:09:59,270
[PHONE RINGING] I'll tell Vic that
myself right after I fire his ass.

219
00:10:01,017 --> 00:10:02,184
Toby, now is not a good time.

220
00:10:02,226 --> 00:10:05,688
It's about Eddie. He and Malcolm went
looking for Dodger and his brothers.

221
00:10:05,730 --> 00:10:07,940
- And they found him.
- What? Where are they?

222
00:10:07,982 --> 00:10:10,276
They're beat up, Archie. Bad.

223
00:10:10,318 --> 00:10:12,612
Eddie's in the hospital. Again.

224
00:10:14,947 --> 00:10:16,616
What'd you find out, Charles?

225
00:10:16,657 --> 00:10:18,951
Our hunch was right.

226
00:10:18,993 --> 00:10:22,455
The calls received by Polly and
Alice came from the same place.

227
00:10:22,496 --> 00:10:24,749
Shankshaw Prison.

228
00:10:24,790 --> 00:10:27,752
Charles, something must have
been said on those calls

229
00:10:27,793 --> 00:10:30,921
that made Mom and Polly
enter a trance-like state

230
00:10:30,963 --> 00:10:33,466
that turned them
into deranged killers.

231
00:10:33,507 --> 00:10:35,134
As if they were hypnotized.

232
00:10:35,176 --> 00:10:35,926
I thought the same thing.

233
00:10:35,927 --> 00:10:40,056
And who do we know that uses
auditory cues and hypnotism

234
00:10:40,097 --> 00:10:42,558
to control its members?
The Farm.

235
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,310
Edgar may be dead,

236
00:10:44,352 --> 00:10:46,896
but his lovesick lackey Evelyn
sure isn't.

237
00:10:46,937 --> 00:10:48,314
She's in prison.

238
00:10:49,357 --> 00:10:51,734
Any chance that prison
is Shankshaw?

239
00:11:04,372 --> 00:11:06,499
[MAN] You hold it
right there, boy.

240
00:11:06,540 --> 00:11:08,918
Now, you are trespassing
on private property.

241
00:11:08,959 --> 00:11:11,295
If you're Forsythe Jones
the First,

242
00:11:11,337 --> 00:11:12,672
then I'm your grandson.

243
00:11:16,217 --> 00:11:18,469
I... I... I... I guess...

244
00:11:18,511 --> 00:11:20,096
you'd better come in, then.

245
00:11:26,936 --> 00:11:28,104
Jason,

246
00:11:28,938 --> 00:11:30,022
Julian,

247
00:11:31,273 --> 00:11:32,900
thank you for
joining me, brothers.

248
00:11:33,818 --> 00:11:36,696
[SIGHS] The day
has finally come.

249
00:11:36,737 --> 00:11:39,699
I'm ending our
collective misery today.

250
00:11:39,740 --> 00:11:42,219
The Chernobyl-grade roach bombs
I've set up throughout Thistlehouse

251
00:11:42,243 --> 00:11:44,412
are discharging a toxin
strong enough to kill anything

252
00:11:44,453 --> 00:11:46,122
that crawls within these walls.

253
00:11:48,958 --> 00:11:50,501
I was born in poison...

254
00:11:53,337 --> 00:11:54,964
and I shall die in poison.

255
00:11:56,716 --> 00:11:58,175
[GAS HISSING]

256
00:12:02,263 --> 00:12:03,723
[CREAKING]

257
00:12:03,764 --> 00:12:05,975
[COUGHING]

258
00:12:11,147 --> 00:12:12,356
Mumzie,

259
00:12:13,065 --> 00:12:14,275
what a surprise.

260
00:12:15,526 --> 00:12:16,652
[BODY THUDS]

261
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:23,200
Whatever your dad said about me

262
00:12:24,326 --> 00:12:26,704
is probably true.

263
00:12:26,746 --> 00:12:29,206
I'm actually not here
to talk about that.

264
00:12:29,248 --> 00:12:30,499
Yet.

265
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:35,421
I'm here to talk about
one of your old classmates,

266
00:12:36,255 --> 00:12:37,840
Francis DuPont.

267
00:12:37,882 --> 00:12:40,926
Well, I remember Francis,
all right.

268
00:12:40,968 --> 00:12:43,846
Look, I think you wrote the
original Baxter Brothers book,

269
00:12:43,888 --> 00:12:45,347
not DuPont.

270
00:12:45,389 --> 00:12:47,391
I think he stole your idea

271
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:49,769
and then he published it
under his name.

272
00:12:49,810 --> 00:12:51,854
Oh, you got it all figured
out, haven't you, boy?

273
00:12:53,314 --> 00:12:55,608
Except your facts,
little mixed up.

274
00:12:58,694 --> 00:13:00,362
Well, why don't you help me
sort them out?

275
00:13:01,655 --> 00:13:03,324
Eddie and Malcolm
are in the hospital.

276
00:13:03,365 --> 00:13:05,951
Munroe is with them,
they went after the Dickenson brothers.

277
00:13:05,993 --> 00:13:08,454
Bill and Fagan beat the
living hell out of those kids.

278
00:13:08,496 --> 00:13:10,539
- I'm not gonna let that go.
- All right.

279
00:13:11,582 --> 00:13:12,708
All right, then.

280
00:13:13,918 --> 00:13:15,419
Your dad would
pound the tar out of me

281
00:13:15,461 --> 00:13:17,230
if I let you do this on your
own, but this is it.

282
00:13:17,254 --> 00:13:18,088
We handle these Dickenson boys

283
00:13:18,130 --> 00:13:22,051
and then you're putting this
vigilante business to bed, all of it.

284
00:13:22,092 --> 00:13:25,095
If I agree, will you help me?

285
00:13:25,846 --> 00:13:27,014
Yeah.

286
00:13:28,724 --> 00:13:30,351
Just let me get changed first.

287
00:13:35,022 --> 00:13:36,273
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

288
00:13:42,196 --> 00:13:43,572
Well, lookie here.

289
00:13:43,614 --> 00:13:45,282
Bill and Fagan Dickenson.

290
00:13:45,324 --> 00:13:48,536
You guys are the scum of the earth.
Going after kids.

291
00:13:49,328 --> 00:13:50,496
[SPITS]

292
00:13:54,875 --> 00:13:56,752
[FP] Big man, huh?

293
00:13:56,794 --> 00:13:58,546
Beating up teenagers.

294
00:14:00,548 --> 00:14:03,092
Let's see how you do against
someone your own size.

295
00:14:04,718 --> 00:14:05,904
I'll break your bones, old man.

296
00:14:05,928 --> 00:14:06,968
Not before we break yours.

297
00:14:08,639 --> 00:14:09,765
[GRUNTS]

298
00:14:12,142 --> 00:14:13,769
Time to
rise and shine, mother dear.

299
00:14:13,811 --> 00:14:14,979
[COUGHS]

300
00:14:20,192 --> 00:14:23,153
Cheryl. What...

301
00:14:23,195 --> 00:14:26,574
Did you really think I was
gassing myself to an early grave?

302
00:14:26,615 --> 00:14:29,201
No. That was a ruse.

303
00:14:29,243 --> 00:14:30,911
But riddle me this, Mumzie.

304
00:14:32,121 --> 00:14:34,248
Do you remember
when I was a little girl,

305
00:14:34,290 --> 00:14:36,876
and you used to read me Alice's
Adventures in Wonderland?

306
00:14:36,917 --> 00:14:39,378
Cheryl, you release me
this minute!

307
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:41,463
You would ask me
if I thought I was Alice.

308
00:14:41,505 --> 00:14:45,217
And I would say, "No,
Mother, I'm the Red Queen."

309
00:14:47,303 --> 00:14:49,013
So as the Red Queen
did to Alice,

310
00:14:49,054 --> 00:14:51,056
I am putting you on trial.

311
00:14:52,349 --> 00:14:53,976
Lunatic child.

312
00:14:55,436 --> 00:14:56,645
What are the charges?

313
00:14:56,687 --> 00:14:58,564
They are as follows.

314
00:14:58,606 --> 00:14:59,999
Prolonged gaslighting in hopes
of driving me cuckoo-bananas,

315
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,751
Prolonged gaslighting in hopes
of driving me cuckoo-bananas,

316
00:15:01,775 --> 00:15:05,571
attempted murder of Archie,
Betty, Veronica and Jughead,

317
00:15:05,613 --> 00:15:08,073
and actual murder of my father,

318
00:15:08,115 --> 00:15:10,910
Clifford Blossom,
Claudius Blossom,

319
00:15:10,951 --> 00:15:12,745
and Hal Cooper among others.

320
00:15:14,830 --> 00:15:16,498
How do you plead,
mother most foul?

321
00:15:19,752 --> 00:15:21,295
I got to say,

322
00:15:23,130 --> 00:15:24,423
that felt good.

323
00:15:25,174 --> 00:15:26,550
Yeah?

324
00:15:26,592 --> 00:15:28,594
- We kicked ass, Mr. Jones.
- Mm-hmm.

325
00:15:30,638 --> 00:15:34,475
It's been a while since these fists
delivered some proper street justice.

326
00:15:35,976 --> 00:15:38,437
The old jacket
still fits like a glove.

327
00:15:38,479 --> 00:15:40,606
- [CHUCKLES]
- And your old man,

328
00:15:40,648 --> 00:15:43,859
he's looking down on us,
probably shaking his head, but...

329
00:15:45,819 --> 00:15:47,196
still...

330
00:15:50,282 --> 00:15:52,910
he'd be glad your
crime-fighting days are over.

331
00:15:55,871 --> 00:15:58,040
[FORSYTHE] And I always
loved detective stories,

332
00:15:58,082 --> 00:16:01,126
so, uh, I come up
with this notion

333
00:16:01,168 --> 00:16:03,921
to write a book
about teenage detectives.

334
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:05,297
Right, the Baxter Brothers.

335
00:16:05,339 --> 00:16:06,650
So how did
DuPont steal it from you?

336
00:16:06,674 --> 00:16:09,134
[SCOFFS] You're getting
ahead of the story here.

337
00:16:09,176 --> 00:16:12,471
You see, I was burning out
at Stonewall,

338
00:16:12,513 --> 00:16:14,473
so, uh, I quit.

339
00:16:15,849 --> 00:16:19,269
The only thing I had
to show for it all is this

340
00:16:19,311 --> 00:16:22,356
one Baxter Brothers story.

341
00:16:22,398 --> 00:16:25,359
I didn't know what to do with it.
Francis said he did.

342
00:16:25,401 --> 00:16:26,860
He offered to buy it from me.

343
00:16:26,902 --> 00:16:27,902
How much?

344
00:16:28,779 --> 00:16:29,989
$5,000.

345
00:16:30,030 --> 00:16:31,615
$5,000?

346
00:16:31,657 --> 00:16:33,617
That franchise is worth
millions now.

347
00:16:33,659 --> 00:16:37,121
Over the years, When I saw how
popular Baxter Brothers became,

348
00:16:37,162 --> 00:16:39,081
I grew bitter,

349
00:16:39,123 --> 00:16:42,751
started drinking and took
my anger out on the world,

350
00:16:43,961 --> 00:16:45,838
and on my son.

351
00:16:45,879 --> 00:16:49,341
Eventually I figured it'd be best
for all concerned if I just...

352
00:16:49,383 --> 00:16:51,361
Went out for a pack of
cigarettes and didn't come back?

353
00:16:51,385 --> 00:16:52,428
Yeah.

354
00:16:54,555 --> 00:16:56,306
[SCOFFS]

355
00:16:56,348 --> 00:16:58,559
Mr. DuPont asked me
to be the next ghostwriter.

356
00:16:58,600 --> 00:16:59,768
Is that a fact?

357
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:02,354
All this time, I...

358
00:17:04,815 --> 00:17:07,192
I had thought that Mr. DuPont
was killing people

359
00:17:07,234 --> 00:17:09,546
in order to keep the secret
that he stole the book from you.

360
00:17:09,570 --> 00:17:12,865
[CHUCKLES] That's quite
the theory there.

361
00:17:12,906 --> 00:17:15,868
If that was the case,
he would have killed me too, wouldn't he?

362
00:17:16,243 --> 00:17:18,620
Yeah. Yes.

363
00:17:18,662 --> 00:17:20,414
A word of advice for you.

364
00:17:21,665 --> 00:17:24,001
I messed up my life.

365
00:17:24,043 --> 00:17:25,961
I messed up your father's life.

366
00:17:27,379 --> 00:17:31,341
You seize the opportunities
you're being given.

367
00:17:33,594 --> 00:17:35,888
- [PRISON DOOR BUZZES]
- Took you long enough.

368
00:17:35,929 --> 00:17:39,016
You weaponized
my family against me

369
00:17:39,058 --> 00:17:43,687
by calling them and triggering
some post-hypnotic suggestion.

370
00:17:44,772 --> 00:17:46,732
What's the directive?

371
00:17:46,774 --> 00:17:49,943
How exactly are you getting
your sleeper cells to turn?

372
00:17:49,985 --> 00:17:53,238
When I deliver the activation,
the receiver turns

373
00:17:53,280 --> 00:17:54,323
into you.

374
00:17:54,364 --> 00:17:55,783
What the hell does that mean?

375
00:17:55,824 --> 00:17:58,077
They become Betty.

376
00:17:58,118 --> 00:18:00,662
As in, Betty Cooper,

377
00:18:00,704 --> 00:18:01,830
as in,

378
00:18:01,872 --> 00:18:02,414
you.

379
00:18:02,456 --> 00:18:05,250
Why did Polly attack
a nurse named Betty?

380
00:18:05,292 --> 00:18:06,752
Why did my mom come after me?

381
00:18:06,794 --> 00:18:08,837
When triggered,
they become Betty.

382
00:18:08,879 --> 00:18:10,756
They try to kill dark Betty,

383
00:18:10,798 --> 00:18:13,842
evil Betty, other Betty.

384
00:18:13,884 --> 00:18:16,845
You mean they try to murder me.

385
00:18:16,887 --> 00:18:18,597
Elegant, isn't it?

386
00:18:21,016 --> 00:18:22,601
It was Edgar's idea.

387
00:18:24,228 --> 00:18:25,604
When they hear the trigger word,

388
00:18:25,646 --> 00:18:26,855
they become you.

389
00:18:26,897 --> 00:18:28,774
And therefore, try to kill you.

390
00:18:28,816 --> 00:18:30,567
You're a psycho.

391
00:18:30,609 --> 00:18:32,528
[EVELYN] Mm-hmm.

392
00:18:32,569 --> 00:18:35,572
So what exactly is
the trigger word, Evelyn?

393
00:18:37,866 --> 00:18:39,118
Tangerine.

394
00:18:39,910 --> 00:18:41,787
Repeated three times in a row.

395
00:18:45,332 --> 00:18:46,416
Tangerine.

396
00:18:48,502 --> 00:18:49,837
Tangerine.

397
00:18:51,755 --> 00:18:52,798
Tan...

398
00:19:00,222 --> 00:19:03,392
- What do you say we call it a night, Red?
- [SHOP BELL JINGLES]

399
00:19:03,433 --> 00:19:05,269
You need a ride
back to the center?

400
00:19:07,980 --> 00:19:09,314
Mr. Jones.

401
00:19:09,773 --> 00:19:10,858
[GUN COCKS]

402
00:19:11,984 --> 00:19:13,902
- [GRUNTS]
- [PEOPLE SCREAMING]

403
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:17,072
[FP GROANING]

404
00:19:26,373 --> 00:19:27,749
I can't believe it.

405
00:19:27,791 --> 00:19:29,835
Mr. Jones, I'm so sorry.

406
00:19:30,544 --> 00:19:33,005
For what? Hey.

407
00:19:33,046 --> 00:19:34,923
It'll take a whole lot more
than a flesh wound

408
00:19:34,965 --> 00:19:37,009
for me to regret
what we did tonight.

409
00:19:37,050 --> 00:19:38,677
It was Dodger Dickenson.

410
00:19:38,719 --> 00:19:39,928
We don't know that.

411
00:19:39,970 --> 00:19:40,804
Yeah, we do.

412
00:19:40,805 --> 00:19:44,224
Word on the street,
it was Dodger and his crazy-ass mom Darla.

413
00:19:44,266 --> 00:19:46,935
That was a parting shot before
the Dickensons get out of town.

414
00:19:46,977 --> 00:19:48,163
So they're still in Riverdale?

415
00:19:48,187 --> 00:19:49,479
Yep. Loading out the arcade.

416
00:19:49,521 --> 00:19:51,361
How about you keep
your damn mouth shut, Fangs?

417
00:19:51,398 --> 00:19:53,775
You're already on thin ice with me.
And you,

418
00:19:53,817 --> 00:19:56,403
you don't even think about it, Red.
We talked about this.

419
00:19:56,445 --> 00:19:59,198
You agreed to
hang it up for good. Hey!

420
00:19:59,239 --> 00:20:00,000
They're leaving town. Archie!

421
00:20:00,001 --> 00:20:01,366
They're leaving town. Archie!

422
00:20:05,120 --> 00:20:07,456
I left before she could
say it a third time.

423
00:20:07,497 --> 00:20:11,043
But what the hell would happen if I
heard the trigger word three times?

424
00:20:11,084 --> 00:20:13,921
Would I be activated
and wanna kill myself?

425
00:20:13,962 --> 00:20:15,631
One way to find out.

426
00:20:16,757 --> 00:20:17,799
We try it here.

427
00:20:19,927 --> 00:20:22,262
Tangerine. Tangerine.

428
00:20:23,764 --> 00:20:24,973
Tangerine.

429
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:32,898
I don't understand.

430
00:20:32,940 --> 00:20:34,191
Nothing happened.

431
00:20:35,359 --> 00:20:38,237
Maybe because
you're already Betty?

432
00:20:38,278 --> 00:20:41,657
Well, the good news is,
you're officially not a ticking time bomb.

433
00:20:43,575 --> 00:20:46,328
Why must we endure this farce?

434
00:20:46,370 --> 00:20:48,205
It's clear no matter what I say,

435
00:20:48,247 --> 00:20:50,290
you're just looking for
a reason to kill me, Cheryl.

436
00:20:50,332 --> 00:20:53,001
On the contrary, Mumzie,

437
00:20:54,461 --> 00:20:56,922
despite your
wicked machinations,

438
00:20:56,964 --> 00:20:59,091
I'm looking for
a reason to spare

439
00:20:59,466 --> 00:21:00,509
your life.

440
00:21:01,301 --> 00:21:02,678
You're my mother.

441
00:21:03,845 --> 00:21:05,889
And yet, you've always
been so cruel to me...

442
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:09,142
For why?

443
00:21:11,853 --> 00:21:14,815
You brutalized me
my entire life.

444
00:21:14,856 --> 00:21:17,025
You tried to kill my friends,

445
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:19,403
and then you hid in Thistlehouse
to keep torturing me.

446
00:21:21,613 --> 00:21:24,133
You saw me happy with Toni and you
couldn't let that be, could you?

447
00:21:24,157 --> 00:21:25,409
[LAUGHS]

448
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:29,621
It wasn't your happiness
with the she-goblin

449
00:21:29,663 --> 00:21:31,915
that I wanted to destroy.

450
00:21:31,957 --> 00:21:34,876
It was your happiness
with Jason.

451
00:21:34,918 --> 00:21:37,963
How can I live knowing
that you are happy

452
00:21:38,005 --> 00:21:40,632
with my dead son?

453
00:21:40,674 --> 00:21:44,219
You don't get what I can't have!

454
00:21:44,261 --> 00:21:46,847
In that case, Mumzie,

455
00:21:46,888 --> 00:21:49,725
you're guilty of
the worst crime of all:

456
00:21:50,892 --> 00:21:53,895
Being hateful to
your rotten core.

457
00:21:53,937 --> 00:21:57,316
Hmm. So, there.
You've condemned me.

458
00:21:58,358 --> 00:21:59,359
[SIGHS]

459
00:21:59,401 --> 00:22:00,694
Execute me, then.

460
00:22:02,029 --> 00:22:03,572
Or cart me off to prison.

461
00:22:03,613 --> 00:22:05,324
Oh no.

462
00:22:05,365 --> 00:22:08,744
Not jail. At least not
in the traditional sense.

463
00:22:08,785 --> 00:22:10,996
You're going to a place

464
00:22:11,038 --> 00:22:15,667
so vile, so revolting,

465
00:22:15,709 --> 00:22:18,920
you'll wish you were bricked up
in Thistlehouse's walls.

466
00:22:20,213 --> 00:22:23,133
TT, prepare the chloroform.

467
00:22:25,510 --> 00:22:26,845
[MUSIC PLAYING FAINTLY]

468
00:22:26,887 --> 00:22:27,554
Thanks.

469
00:22:27,596 --> 00:22:30,974
You're dressed to kill me, huh?
Am I in any danger?

470
00:22:31,016 --> 00:22:32,434
Not tonight.

471
00:22:32,476 --> 00:22:35,437
Just cutting loose before
the clock strikes 12.

472
00:22:35,479 --> 00:22:38,231
- [HIRAM] Mm.
- [REGGIE] Hey, Ronnie.

473
00:22:38,273 --> 00:22:41,360
You got someone asking for you.
Says it's official.

474
00:22:55,707 --> 00:22:58,227
Are you a bourbon gal?
I can whip you up a killer old-fashioned.

475
00:22:58,251 --> 00:22:59,753
Veronica Luna,

476
00:23:01,254 --> 00:23:02,964
I'm Shoshana Rutherford.

477
00:23:03,924 --> 00:23:05,384
The recruiter from Columbia?

478
00:23:07,010 --> 00:23:09,638
What are you doing here? I...
My interview's on Monday.

479
00:23:09,679 --> 00:23:12,474
Your assistant
called my assistant,

480
00:23:12,516 --> 00:23:14,226
and requested that I come down

481
00:23:14,267 --> 00:23:17,229
