♪ Gonna set this dance alight ♪

511
00:25:09,591 --> 00:25:13,011
♪ Well, they're packed
Pretty tight in here tonight ♪

512
00:25:13,053 --> 00:25:16,181
♪ I'm looking for a dolly
Who will see me right ♪

513
00:25:16,223 --> 00:25:19,351
♪ I may use a little muscle
To get what I need ♪

514
00:25:19,392 --> 00:25:22,771
♪ I may sink a little drink And
shout out "She's with me!" ♪

515
00:25:22,812 --> 00:25:25,690
♪ A couple of the sounds
That I really like ♪

516
00:25:25,732 --> 00:25:28,860
♪ Are the sounds of
A switchblade and a motorbike ♪

517
00:25:28,902 --> 00:25:31,863
♪ I'm a juvenile product
Of the working class ♪

518
00:25:31,905 --> 00:25:35,617
♪ Whose best friend floats
In the bottom of a glass ♪

519
00:25:35,659 --> 00:25:38,828
♪ Oh ♪

520
00:25:38,870 --> 00:25:41,706
♪ Don't give us none
Of your aggravation ♪

521
00:25:41,748 --> 00:25:44,709
♪ We had it
With your discipline ♪

522
00:25:44,751 --> 00:25:48,255
♪ Saturday night's
All right for fighting ♪

523
00:25:48,296 --> 00:25:51,132
♪ Get a little action in ♪

524
00:25:51,174 --> 00:25:54,261
♪ Get about as oiled
As a diesel train ♪

525
00:25:54,302 --> 00:25:56,930
♪ Gonna set
This dance alight... ♪

526
00:25:56,972 --> 00:25:58,306
Stop!

527
00:25:58,765 --> 00:25:59,975
You'll kill him!

528
00:26:02,435 --> 00:26:05,438
I told Dodger,
if we ever fought again,

529
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:06,856
he wouldn't be able to walk.

530
00:26:06,898 --> 00:26:09,109
So you drag his ass
out of here, Darla.

531
00:26:09,150 --> 00:26:11,027
And if you or any of your sons

532
00:26:11,069 --> 00:26:12,445
step foot in this town
ever again,

533
00:26:12,487 --> 00:26:14,239
I'll kill all of you.

534
00:26:14,281 --> 00:26:15,115
[BOY] Archie.

535
00:26:15,116 --> 00:26:21,204
♪ Saturday, Saturday, Saturday
Saturday night's all right ♪

536
00:26:22,497 --> 00:26:23,373
[MUSIC STOPS]

537
00:26:23,415 --> 00:26:25,166
[ALL CHEERING]

538
00:26:30,463 --> 00:26:31,673
[MAN] Love you!

539
00:26:35,302 --> 00:26:37,721
Well, I hope
the song and dance was fun,

540
00:26:37,762 --> 00:26:41,266
'cause at midnight,
you turn back into Cenicienta.

541
00:26:41,308 --> 00:26:43,435
And all this, it goes away.

542
00:26:43,476 --> 00:26:45,854
I may not be able to serve rum,

543
00:26:45,895 --> 00:26:48,106
but that won't stop me
from making it

544
00:26:48,148 --> 00:26:49,441
and burying you.

545
00:26:49,482 --> 00:26:51,443
Hmm. About that.

546
00:26:52,986 --> 00:26:54,321
Do you know what this is?

547
00:26:54,362 --> 00:26:55,113
It's a patent.

548
00:26:55,114 --> 00:26:58,366
That rum recipe that my
mother so graciously gave you,

549
00:26:59,200 --> 00:27:00,285
I own it.

550
00:27:00,327 --> 00:27:01,953
So if you use it to make rum,

551
00:27:01,995 --> 00:27:04,205
I will sue you
for everything you have.

552
00:27:05,248 --> 00:27:08,293
Oh, and good luck
with your interview.

553
00:27:08,335 --> 00:27:10,211
I can't wait to hear
what Columbia thinks about

554
00:27:10,253 --> 00:27:12,756
underage party girl
Veronica Luna.

555
00:27:13,840 --> 00:27:14,883
Mm.

556
00:27:35,779 --> 00:27:36,779
Hello.

557
00:27:37,530 --> 00:27:38,740
Hello.

558
00:27:39,532 --> 00:27:41,660
Are you here to kill me

559
00:27:41,701 --> 00:27:43,578
like I killed Caramel?

560
00:28:30,250 --> 00:28:32,877
I leave you alone for one day
and you get shot.

561
00:28:32,919 --> 00:28:35,505
Well, I've had worse and I'll
be home tomorrow morning.

562
00:28:35,547 --> 00:28:37,298
Where you been anyway?

563
00:28:37,340 --> 00:28:38,925
I should probably
sit down for this.

564
00:28:43,263 --> 00:28:44,639
I, uh...

565
00:28:48,143 --> 00:28:50,478
I found Grandpa.

566
00:28:50,520 --> 00:28:53,773
He's living in Seaside.
He's in a converted bus.

567
00:28:53,815 --> 00:28:56,401
Sounds about right.
What'd you do that for?

568
00:28:56,443 --> 00:28:58,903
Mr. DuPont offered me
the Baxter Brothers contract.

569
00:28:58,945 --> 00:29:01,030
[SCOFFS]

570
00:29:01,072 --> 00:29:04,868
I wanted to talk to Grandpa
before I signed or not.

571
00:29:04,909 --> 00:29:08,037
- And now that you have?
- It turns out I was wrong.

572
00:29:09,789 --> 00:29:13,460
DuPont did steal the idea from
Grandpa, but he did it legally.

573
00:29:15,587 --> 00:29:16,963
And for what it's worth,

574
00:29:18,673 --> 00:29:20,508
he feels bad about the
way he treated you.

575
00:29:22,177 --> 00:29:24,262
He knows what he did
to you and Grandma.

576
00:29:24,304 --> 00:29:26,014
And he knows that
he was a bad father.

577
00:29:26,055 --> 00:29:27,807
Yeah, that he was.

578
00:29:27,849 --> 00:29:30,286
But maybe this wild goose chase I
went on could be worth something.

579
00:29:30,310 --> 00:29:32,312
Like what?

580
00:29:32,353 --> 00:29:34,634
Would you be willing to talk
to him if I brought him here?

581
00:29:35,815 --> 00:29:37,317
Doc has me here overnight.

582
00:29:39,402 --> 00:29:40,820
I guess if he wanted to stop by,

583
00:29:40,862 --> 00:29:42,655
couldn't exactly say no...

584
00:29:44,491 --> 00:29:45,742
could I?

585
00:29:50,330 --> 00:29:51,372
Oh.

586
00:29:56,419 --> 00:29:57,629
Hello, Mumzie.

587
00:29:57,670 --> 00:29:58,880
Cheryl?

588
00:30:01,132 --> 00:30:03,176
What is this?

589
00:30:03,218 --> 00:30:04,135
I trust you approve
of this bunker.

590
00:30:04,177 --> 00:30:08,181
After all, it's larger than the cell
you would have gotten at Shankshaw.

591
00:30:08,223 --> 00:30:11,017
With food,
electricity, plumbing.

592
00:30:11,059 --> 00:30:12,811
You wretched child.

593
00:30:12,852 --> 00:30:14,646
You can't keep me... Oh.

594
00:30:14,687 --> 00:30:16,356
On the contrary, Mother,

595
00:30:17,899 --> 00:30:19,526
you need time and solitude

596
00:30:19,567 --> 00:30:21,778
to seek penance
for your crimes and cruelty.

597
00:30:22,278 --> 00:30:23,488
Toodles.

598
00:30:23,530 --> 00:30:25,156
Cheryl. Cheryl.

599
00:30:26,157 --> 00:30:27,408
Chery!

600
00:30:33,581 --> 00:30:36,251
[BETTY] It was terrifying,
Charles.

601
00:30:36,292 --> 00:30:40,171
When I saw the red door,
I fugued.

602
00:30:40,213 --> 00:30:44,050
I slipped into a trance. Why?

603
00:30:44,092 --> 00:30:46,529
I don't know, maybe a combination
of hearing the trigger earlier

604
00:30:46,553 --> 00:30:48,429
and then returning to
a familiar setting.

605
00:30:49,389 --> 00:30:50,765
What I saw,

606
00:30:52,058 --> 00:30:54,686
me about to kill Caramel,

607
00:30:56,563 --> 00:30:59,607
I think that's when the
dark part of me was born.

608
00:31:00,316 --> 00:31:01,025
If that's true,

609
00:31:01,067 --> 00:31:03,862
if you can go back to the
moment of dark Betty's birth

610
00:31:03,903 --> 00:31:05,572
and stop it from happening,

611
00:31:06,406 --> 00:31:07,031
it will essentially be...

612
00:31:07,032 --> 00:31:10,451
Killing my shadow self
before she was even born.

613
00:31:11,619 --> 00:31:12,829
We could try it.

614
00:31:15,832 --> 00:31:16,833
Yeah.

615
00:31:19,294 --> 00:31:20,503
[SIGHS]

616
00:31:20,545 --> 00:31:21,796
Tangerine.

617
00:31:21,838 --> 00:31:24,215
Tangerine. Tangerine.

618
00:31:59,626 --> 00:32:00,668
Wait.

619
00:32:01,878 --> 00:32:04,005
Let me take that from you.

620
00:32:04,047 --> 00:32:06,341
But what am I gonna do now?

621
00:32:06,799 --> 00:32:08,134
You can go play.

622
00:32:08,176 --> 00:32:10,470
Really? I can go and play?

623
00:32:12,138 --> 00:32:13,431
Yeah, go ahead.

624
00:32:14,349 --> 00:32:15,516
Thank you.

625
00:32:29,656 --> 00:32:30,782
[CHARLES] Betty.

626
00:32:33,660 --> 00:32:35,078
I... I...

627
00:32:35,119 --> 00:32:37,038
I'm not sure,
but I think I did it.

628
00:32:37,705 --> 00:32:39,332
Well, that's great news.

629
00:32:39,374 --> 00:32:40,833
You're all right.

630
00:32:41,668 --> 00:32:42,668
You're okay now.

631
00:32:45,546 --> 00:32:47,840
I'm sorry I kept you
waiting, Miss Rutherford.

632
00:32:49,842 --> 00:32:52,971
I'm guessing my shot at
Columbia is pretty much blown.

633
00:32:54,222 --> 00:32:55,974
Not necessarily.

634
00:32:56,015 --> 00:33:00,645
At Columbia, we're always looking
for people with good stories.

635
00:33:00,687 --> 00:33:03,564
I don't know
what happened here tonight,

636
00:33:03,606 --> 00:33:05,233
but I'll bet it's a good story.

637
00:33:07,276 --> 00:33:09,070
It is indeed.

638
00:33:09,112 --> 00:33:11,072
Well, how about
you tell it to me?

639
00:33:12,073 --> 00:33:13,366
[INHALES]

640
00:33:25,712 --> 00:33:27,171
[TONI] Babe, are you okay?

641
00:33:27,213 --> 00:33:29,382
Are you having second
thoughts about your mom?

642
00:33:30,466 --> 00:33:32,510
No, but...

643
00:33:34,971 --> 00:33:37,557
I was ruminating that perhaps...

644
00:33:38,766 --> 00:33:39,851
[SIGHS]

645
00:33:41,853 --> 00:33:43,354
It's time to bury Jason.

646
00:33:46,733 --> 00:33:48,317
Cheryl, are you sure?

647
00:33:56,367 --> 00:33:57,618
Yes.

648
00:33:58,703 --> 00:33:59,746
[SIGHS]

649
00:34:01,080 --> 00:34:03,041
There's been so much pain

650
00:34:03,082 --> 00:34:05,752
and poison in this house.

651
00:34:05,793 --> 00:34:09,547
And Jason, more than any of us,

652
00:34:11,632 --> 00:34:14,802
deserves the peace my mother
spent years denying me.

653
00:34:16,137 --> 00:34:17,555
Archie?

654
00:34:17,597 --> 00:34:19,223
What's going on, honey?

655
00:34:19,265 --> 00:34:20,808
Why are you sitting in the dark?

656
00:34:24,812 --> 00:34:26,314
What happened?

657
00:34:27,106 --> 00:34:28,649
Who did this to you?

658
00:34:30,151 --> 00:34:31,194
I did.

659
00:34:33,112 --> 00:34:34,572
I did it to me, Mom.

660
00:34:35,740 --> 00:34:38,409
The Dickensons
were leaving town.

661
00:34:38,451 --> 00:34:40,078
They were done with Riverdale.

662
00:34:40,119 --> 00:34:42,371
But I wanted to hurt them,
to hurt Dodger.

663
00:34:45,750 --> 00:34:46,918
Maybe even kill him.

664
00:34:46,959 --> 00:34:48,127
Archie.

665
00:34:49,378 --> 00:34:51,589
Doesn't make
any sense to me, Mom,

666
00:34:51,631 --> 00:34:54,425
how predators like Dodger
get to live,

667
00:34:56,803 --> 00:34:58,554
but Dad, he...

668
00:35:02,517 --> 00:35:04,560
[SIGHS]

669
00:35:04,602 --> 00:35:07,414
And the worst part about it is, some
of the kids from the center were there,

670
00:35:07,438 --> 00:35:09,941
and they saw me
standing over him, angry,

671
00:35:11,442 --> 00:35:12,485
bloody,

672
00:35:13,820 --> 00:35:15,947
- and a monster.
- No.

673
00:35:15,988 --> 00:35:17,573
You're not a monster.

674
00:35:18,533 --> 00:35:19,617
You're just...

675
00:35:20,368 --> 00:35:21,536
still hurting.

676
00:35:23,079 --> 00:35:24,789
When will this end, Mom?

677
00:35:28,543 --> 00:35:30,128
How does this end?

678
00:35:32,463 --> 00:35:35,049
I've never felt further
from Dad than I do now.

679
00:35:39,804 --> 00:35:41,055
[MARY SIGHS]

680
00:35:54,861 --> 00:35:57,238
Let me guess, my old man
didn't wanna come.

681
00:35:58,531 --> 00:35:59,532
No.

682
00:36:00,241 --> 00:36:01,241
He ran away.

683
00:36:03,953 --> 00:36:05,413
I'm so sorry.

684
00:36:09,792 --> 00:36:11,169
I feel like a fool.

685
00:36:11,752 --> 00:36:13,296
No, you're not.

686
00:36:15,256 --> 00:36:17,758
You would be if you turned
down that contract, though.

687
00:36:20,344 --> 00:36:21,596
No, I'm signing it.

688
00:36:24,557 --> 00:36:25,933
[SIGHS]

689
00:36:28,686 --> 00:36:30,563
I think it's time
to let go of the past.

690
00:37:05,973 --> 00:37:07,433
Evening, Forsythe.

691
00:37:16,734 --> 00:37:17,818
Oh.

692
00:37:18,778 --> 00:37:20,154
This is the part
where you kill me?

693
00:37:21,447 --> 00:37:23,199
No, you ass.

694
00:37:28,246 --> 00:37:29,455
It's an initiation.

695
00:38:09,161 --> 00:38:11,414
Welcome to the Quill and
Skull Society, Jones.

696
00:38:12,790 --> 00:38:14,667
[ALL APPLAUD]

697
00:38:16,627 --> 00:38:18,129
[PHONE VIBRATING]

698
00:38:23,718 --> 00:38:24,885
Cheryl, what's up?

699
00:38:30,016 --> 00:38:31,642
[CHERYL] Thank you all
for coming.

700
00:38:31,684 --> 00:38:33,978
You all were here last
time I was at this river.

701
00:38:34,937 --> 00:38:36,814
When I tried
to take my own life.

702
00:38:38,941 --> 00:38:40,401
It's only fitting

703
00:38:40,443 --> 00:38:41,902
that you're here now.

704
00:38:42,903 --> 00:38:44,655
[TEARFULLY] My beloved Toni,

705
00:38:44,697 --> 00:38:46,532
as I give Jason,

706
00:38:47,658 --> 00:38:48,993
at long last,

707
00:38:50,411 --> 00:38:52,246
the funeral he deserves.

708
00:39:02,506 --> 00:39:03,674
[CRYING]

709
00:39:20,107 --> 00:39:21,567
[CONTINUES CRYING]

710
00:39:45,216 --> 00:39:47,301
He was a good brother to me.

711
00:39:50,721 --> 00:39:52,973
I wish you could have
met him for real.

712
00:39:53,891 --> 00:39:55,101
I know.

713
00:39:56,894 --> 00:39:58,521
[DOOR BEEPS, OPENS]

714
00:40:01,857 --> 00:40:03,150
[DOOR CLOSES]

715
00:40:12,785 --> 00:40:14,245
[ARCHIE] Yeah?

716
00:40:14,286 --> 00:40:15,704
Can I help you?

717
00:40:15,746 --> 00:40:17,790
Archie? Archie Andrews?

718
00:40:19,250 --> 00:40:20,418
I am.

719
00:40:20,459 --> 00:40:21,669
It's good to see you, son.

720
00:40:22,753 --> 00:40:23,838
My name is Frank.

721
00:40:25,214 --> 00:40:26,340
I'm, uh...

722
00:40:27,675 --> 00:40:29,135
I'm your dad's brother.

723
00:40:56,829 --> 00:40:58,372
Tangerine.

724
00:41:00,040 --> 00:41:01,500
Tangerine.

725
00:41:02,168 --> 00:41:03,377
[GLASS SHATTERS]

726
00:41:03,919 --> 00:41:04,919
Betty.

727
00:41:05,754 --> 00:41:06,797
Honey.

728
00:41:06,839 --> 00:41:08,215
What happened?

729
00:41:11,844 --> 00:41:13,846
I wanted to make sure
that it was gone.

730
00:41:15,139 --> 00:41:16,849
The dark part of myself.

731
00:41:19,059 --> 00:41:20,269
And it was.

732
00:41:42,583 --> 00:41:43,834
He's dead.

733
00:41:45,211 --> 00:41:46,253
What did you do, Betty?

